.kp on
:FED.
4.3 Exceptions
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Accident insurance does not cover the following:
.br
.of 5mm
*¤Accidents attributable to illness or the triggering of a latent
propensity to illness, even though the illness may have arisen and/or been
exacerbated by an accident.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Exacerbation of the consequences of an accident attributable to a
pre-existing or randomly occurring illness.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤The consequences of medical treatment not necessitated by an accident of
the kind covered by the insurance policy.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Personal injury arising from infection with bacteria or a virus.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Dental treatment if the insured has not practised ordinary
dental care, involving regular check-ups and treatment. If the
condition of the teeth or dentures had deteriorated prior to the
accident (for example, as a result of fillings, root canal
treatment, wear, attachment loss, paradentosis or other
diseases), the compensation payable will be reduced or annulled
proportionally to the extent of the deterioration in relation to
well cared-for teeth or dentures.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Dental damage attributable to biting or chewing (eating).
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Any subsequent treatment of previous dental damage paid for by
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
