5.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance covers:
.of 5mm
*¤* treatment and/or repatriation in the event of acute illness or injury
while travelling
.of
.of 5mm
*¤treatment of acute deterioration of an illness/injury, if the insured's
illness/injury was in a good, stable phase prior to departure.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The insurance covers necessary and reasonable expenses for:
.of 5mm
*¤hospital treatment and hospitalisation, including operations and
transport by ambulance to the nearest treatment location.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤* medical treatment and medically prescribed medication, x-rays and
other aids/procedures
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤medical treatment prescribed by a physiotherapist or chiropractor - up
to five treatments abroad for each person insured
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤acute analgesic treatment at a dentist's
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤hotel and meals when an extraordinary stay has been prescribed by a
doctor
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤rejoining the planned route or repatriation when the planned route
cannot be completed on medical grounds, on condition that the insured has
not already been repatriated
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤medically prescribed repatriation or transport to the nearest
appropriate treatment location
.of
.of 5mm
*¤transport of the body of the insured if he/she is deceased, including
expenses for legally required measures.
