:FED.
Pre-existing illness/injury
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the insured has a pre-existing illness/injury, this illness/injury
must have been in a good, stable phase for at least two months prior to
departure.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
In this context, 'a good, stable phase' is taken to indicate that the
condition has been stationary without any kind of change, development or
periodical deterioration that has:
:SKRSLUT.
.br
.of 5mm
*¤required contact with a doctor (over and above regular check-ups)
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤resulted in the adjustment of - or plans to adjust - treatment and/or
medication
.of
.of 5mm
*¤resulted in the scheduling of additional examinations, treatment or
hospitalisation.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
Advance consent
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the insured has a pre-existing illness/injury, he/she can contact
SOS International prior to departure to request advance consent
stating that coverage under this article still applies despite the
illness/injury. Advance consent from SOS International is binding on
Privatsikring.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Medical advance consent is only necessary if the illness/injury of the
insured is not in a good, stable phase two months prior to departure.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Visit www.sos.eu/mf to take a quick and easy test to establish whether
medical advance assessment is necessary. If you do not have Internet
access, you can contact SOS Travel Service on +45 38 48 82 50.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.2 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Payment of compensation is conditional upon all treatment and
transport being performed by arrangement with SOS International. As
such, it is SOS International which decides when and how repatriation
is to take place. Therefore, SOS International must always be
contacted before any kind of treatment or transport is initiated.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
